cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.PL 

The paper discusses a new approach to access control that makes use of formal models and algorithms. This suggests that it could belong to the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), software engineering (cs.SE), databases (cs.DB), and programming languages (cs.PL). However, given the focus on access control and authorization policies, cs.CR and cs.DS are the most likely categories.
